<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Tennessee Storms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LINDEN, Tenn. (AP) -- It may take days to restore power to areas  
hard hit by storms that littered roads with fallen trees and left 
four dead, officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	This tiny town of 1,300 about 70 miles southwest of Nashville  
suffered the worst, with three killed by Wednesday night's storms -- 
a county trustee, a local schoolteacher and a 14-year-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
	``This morning we realized this isn't just something on TV in  
some other city. It hit home this time,'' said Capt. Gary Rogers of 
the county rescue squad. 
</P>
<P>
	Homes were darkened overnight from Memphis to Nashville, with at  
least 60,000 without power, though many areas had power returned by 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The storms crumpled houses, splintered trees and left at least  
53 injured. In all, 30 counties were damaged. 
</P>
<P>
	Fourteen-year-old Brandi Mathis was the only family member  
killed when her home was destroyed. Perry County Trustee Hollis 
Hinson, 47, and schoolteacher Patti Haston, 47, died when his home 
was turned to rubble. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm mad but I don't know who to be mad at,'' said Debbie  
Chandler, looking at the concrete steps which were the only things 
left of Hinson's house. 
</P>
<P>
	A man in Madison County was killed when his pickup truck hit a  
tree that had fallen across a road. 
</P>
<P>
	On Thursday, heavy storms tore roofs off buildings in South  
Carolina and knocked over trees and power lines in Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
	The storms followed Monday's deadly wave of tornadoes in the  
Plains that killed 46. There were also damaging storms Wednesday in 
North Carolina and Georgia. 
</P>
<P>
	In Tennessee, shelter for the homeless was provided by the  
American Red Cross, the Salvation Army and others. 
</P>
<P>
	Some areas would probably wait five days before power was  
restored, and cleanup might take longer, said Cecil Whaley, 
director of natural hazards for the Tennessee Emergency Management 
Agency. Some crews might have to be flown in because fallen trees 
blocked roads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
