<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Auburn Player Innocent on Harassment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Auburn running back Demontray Carter was  
found innocent of misdemeanor harassment charges in Municipal 
Court, while a teammate was granted youthful offender status on 
similar charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Tigers receiver Reggie Worthy, 20, received youthful offender  
status, and his file was sealed Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The charges stemmed from an off-campus party last month. Auburn  
student Canisha Freeman said the two players poured beer on her and 
that Worthy pushed her and struck her in the face. 
</P>
<P>
	Carter, a 21-year-old junior, started six games last season, and  
was the Tigers' second-leading rusher. 
</P>
<P>
	Worthy, a sophomore, sat out last season for academic reasons.  
He emerged from spring practices as a starting wide receiver. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
