<HEADLINE> European Interest Rates Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) -- The European Central Bank left its key  
interest rate unchanged at 2.5 percent at its regular meeting 
Thursday, as was widely expected. 
</P>
<P>
	The bank cut the rate by half a percentage point a month ago,  
the first reduction since it took over monetary policy for the 11 
European Union nations that adopted the euro currency on Jan. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	It said at the time that that cut, which was bigger than  
expected, would be the last for the foreseeable future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
