<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-06 22:05:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cardinals Pitcher Injured Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Often-injured St. Louis Cardinals pitcher  
Donovan Osborne may be headed for the disabled list again. 
</P>
<P>
	Osborne, who missed most of the last two seasons due to assorted  
injuries, left Thursday night's 13-3 loss to Pittsburgh after four 
innings with tightness in his shoulder. He's already been on the 
disabled list six times and missed the entire 1994 season after 
reconstructive shoulder surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Osborne (1-3) wasn't sure when he was hurt. He threw 75 pitches  
and allowed four runs on seven hits. 
</P>
<P>
	``When you're in the heat of the battle, you try to do what you  
can out there,'' Osborne said. ``It just really tightened up that 
last inning. That's it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Osborne, 29, has started only 14 games each of the last two  
seasons because of a hernia, two groin injuries and a shoulder 
injury. He wasn't optimistic about making his next start on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not sure,'' he said. ``I'll just pray.''  
</P>
<P>
	Manager Tony La Russa already has a game plan for doing without  
him, with Manny Aybar replacing him in the rotation. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was in the heat of the moment in the game and he said, `I  
couldn't go any longer,''' La Russa said. ``He indicated he had 
some problems, so we'll get a doctor in to check him and see what 
it all means.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Aybar, who has thrown 11 consecutive scoreless innings of  
relief, actually is a good bet to fill in for Kent Mercker on 
Sunday. Mercker threw 3 2-3 innings of relief on Thursday and 
allowed four earned runs, but would likely stay in the rotation 
despite a 7.48 ERA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
