<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NBC Extends Breeders' Cup Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- NBC has extended its contract to broadcast  
the Breeders' Cup championship through 2001, the Breeders' Cup said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The network's five-year deal to broadcast the championship races  
was to have expired after this year's Breeders' Cup on Nov. 6 at 
Gulfstream Park in Hallandale, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
	NBC has broadcast every Breeders' Cup since the event's  
inception in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're very pleased to continue broadcasting one of the great  
days in American sport,'' NBC Sports president Ken Schanzer said. 
``The Breeders' Cup is one of a select few events created within 
the past 30 years that has become a major championship. We look 
forward to further strengthening our association with the Breeders' 
Cup through this extension.'' 
</P>
<P>
	NBC recently announced it will broadcast four one-hour ``Road to  
the Breeders' Cup'' programs this fall. Those broadcasts will 
feature major stakes races leading up to the day of championship 
races. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials declined to discuss financial terms of the contract  
extension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
