<HEADLINE> April, Year-to-Date Retail Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	April sales and sales for the fiscal year to date reported by  
leading retailers. 
</P>
<P>
	The sales compare the current year's sales with those of the  
previous year. Retailers are ranked according to results at the end 
of April. 
</P>
<P>
	Reporting periods vary slightly. Most retailers' fiscal years  
end in late January or early February. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales include those from stores open at least a year, also known  
as same-store or comparable store sales, and total sales. Retailers 
release only percentage changes for same-store sales, while they 
provide dollar figures and percentages for total sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Securities analysts and investors believe same-store sales  
provide a more accurate assessment of a retailer's performance than 
total sales. 

</P>
<P>
 *Wal-Mart Stores Inc.  
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended April 30: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 4.6 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $11.01 billion, up 11.5 percent from $9.88  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Three months ended April 30: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 8.9 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $35.61 billion, up 15.9 percent from $30.72  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Sears, Roebuck and Co.	
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 0.9 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.04 billion, down 4.3 percent from $3.17  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Three months ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 0.7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $9.28 billion, down 3.3 percent from $9.59  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Kmart Corp.	
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended April 28: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 5.7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $2.75 billion, up 7.3 percent from $2.56  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Three months ended April 28: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 6.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $8.14 billion, up 8.4 percent from $7.52  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *J.C. Penney Co. Inc.	
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 0.2 percent at Penney stores only.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $2.34 billion, up 6.7 percent from $2.19  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Three months ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 0.5 percent at Penney stores only.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $7.57 billion, up 7.4 percent from $7.05  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	(Total sales include J.C. Penney stores, its catalog and drug  
stores, including recently acquired drug chains.) 
</P>
<P>
 *Dayton Hudson Corp.	
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 1.3 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $2.09 billion, up 2.9 percent from $2.03  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Three months ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $6.99 billion, up 11.7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
 *Federated Department Stores Inc.	
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 1.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $1.25 billion, up 12.9 percent from $1.11  
billion. (Total sales include the revenues from the direct-seller 
Fingerhut, which was acquired in March).	
</P>
<P>
 *Three months ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 4.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.71 billion, up 7.3 percent from $3.46  
billion. (Total sales include the revenues from the direct-seller 
Fingerhut, which was acquired in March).	
</P>
<P>
 *May Department Stores Co.	
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 7.7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $954.3 billion, up 12.3 percent from $849  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Three months ended May 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 3.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $2.95 billion, up 8 percent from $2.72 billion.  
</P>
<P>
 *Dillard's Inc.	
