<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Nightclub Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EL MONTE, Calif. (AP) -- A gunman shot a man to death today at a  
nightclub after an argument, then sprayed the booth where the 
victim was sitting with bullets and killed three of the five others 
seated there. 
</P>
<P>
	The shooting happened about 1:45 a.m. in the International Club  
in El Monte, about 12 miles east of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	The gunman had argued with one of the victims and returned with  
a semiautomatic handgun, said Los Angeles County sheriff's Lt. Ray 
Peavy. 
</P>
<P>
	The man with whom he had argued was shot in the head, while two  
men and a woman sitting nearby were sprayed with gunfire, Peavy 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``As soon as he shot him, he reportedly just continued firing  
the gun at will and hit the other three victims, who just happened 
to be sitting there,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Two women also seated in the booth were not injured.  
</P>
<P>
	Peavy said it's not uncommon for patrons to share one of the  
club's large horseshoe-shaped booths even if they don't know each 
another. 
</P>
<P>
	At least 15 other patrons were inside the club when the shooting  
occurred. 
</P>
<P>
	The gunman fled after the shooting and remained free hours  
later, but he may have been videotaped by a surveillance camera. 
Sheriff's technicians worked this morning to enhance the video in 
hopes of getting a better image of the suspect, Peavy said. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators compiled a description of the gunman from  
witnesses, who did not know the man's name, Peavy said. The cause 
of the argument that led to the shooting was unknown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
