<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Sniper Rifle Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- In a May 3 story about .50-caliber sniper  
rifles, The Associated Press reported erroneously that such weapons 
are capable of penetrating a tank's armor from a mile away and were 
used against Iraqi tanks during the Persian Gulf War. 
</P>
<P>
	Such rifles were used against Iraqi armored personnel carriers,  
bunkers and other military vehicles but would not normally be 
effective against modern tanks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
