<HEADLINE> Brigham Young 3, Penn State 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- All-Americans Ossie Antonetti and Ryan Millar  
overcame intestinal illness to lead Brigham Young to a 10-15, 15-4, 
15-11, 15-4 victory over Penn State in the opening semifinal of the 
NCAA men's volleyball championship Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	In the oxther semifinal at UCLA's Pauley Pavilion, Long Beach  
State played Indiana-Purdue of Fort Wayne. The winners meet 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Top-seeded BYU (29-1) was led by Antonetti's 24 kills and  
Millar's 20. 
</P>
<P>
	Brigham Young coach Carl McGown said both players had been  
suffering Wednesday from ``intense intestinal distress'' and it was 
questionable whether they would play. 
</P>
<P>
	Brad Miller led Penn State (22-13) with 20 kills.  
</P>
<P>
	BYU's loss in the opening game of the match was only its third  
in its past 33 games. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cougars broke out to an 8-1 lead in the second game and an  
8-4 advantage in the third. The Nittany Lions responded with five 
consecutive points. After Millar's kill gave the serve back to 
Brigham Young, the Cougars regained the lead on Rich Lambourne's 
kill, eventually increasing their advantage to 12-9. Penn State won 
the next two points, but the Cougars closed the game with the final 
three points. 
</P>
<P>
	Brigham Young also got off to a fast start in the fourth game,  
8-1. Following two Nittany Lions points, the Cougars scored the 
next four for a commanding 12-3 lead, and closed it out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
