<HEADLINE> Trainer: Kelly Kip Is Recovering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Kelly Kip, one of thoroughbred racing's top  
sprinters, was on his way to a full recovery from a serious leg 
joint infection, trainer H. Allen Jerkens said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The infection was considered career and perhaps life-threatening  
only a week ago. Kelly Kip was scratched from last Sunday's Carter 
Handicap because of the injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Treatment at Dr. Dennis Milne's veterinary clinic has been  
successful, Jerkens said, adding the horse ``is OK. They had him 
out grazing and walking.'' 
</P>
<P>
	No date has been set for Kelly Kip's return to his barn at  
Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	In his last race, on April 10, the 5-year-old Kelly Kip broke  
his own Aqueduct record for six furlongs in winning the $100,000 
Bold Ruler Stakes by 2 1/2 lengths over Artax. 
</P>
<P>
	Kelly Kip's time of 1:07 2-5 clipped 1-5 of a second off the  
mark he set on April 11, 1998. 
</P>
