<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> USA Today To Run Ads on Page One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARLINGTON, Va. (AP) -- USA Today plans to begin running ads along  
the bottom of page one. 
</P>
<P>
	The one-inch tall ads will run the width of the page, the  
newspaper said Wednesday. The first will appear Oct. 1. 
</P>
<P>
	The space was recently offered to advertisers in one-year  
contracts. AT&AMP;T, Marriott and Northwest Airlines are among the 
clients that have committed to placing ads, the newspaper said. The 
ads for each company will run on one designated day of the week. 
</P>
<P>
	USA Today has an average daily circulation of 2.3 million.  
</P>
<P>
	European newspapers often run advertising on their front pages.  
But American papers have not adopted the practice, although The New 
York Times has long run classified advertising of up to four lines 
on its front page. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
