<HEADLINE> Saberhagen Leaves Game With Pain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Boston Red Sox right-hander Bret Saberhagen, who  
returned after missing his last start with stiffness in his 
shoulder, left tonight's game against Texas with tightness in his 
right shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Saberhagen, who left his start April 24 against Cleveland with  
stiffness in his shoulder, allowed just three hits, while striking 
out five and not walking a batter in a scoreless, 43-pitch effort. 
