<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Eddie Jones Has Hand Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Charlotte Hornets guard Eddie Jones  
underwent surgery today to repair injuries he suffered when his 
hand hit the rim during an attempted shot block last month. 
</P>
<P>
	A surgeon repaired a flexor tendon, an artery and a nerve in  
Jones' right hand, the team said in a statement. The procedure was 
performed by Dr. Alan Ward at Carolinas Medical Center in 
Charlotte, the Hornets said. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones' fingers will be in a splint for six weeks and he'll  
undergo an additional six weeks of rehabilitation. He is expected 
to be ready for training camp next season. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury occurred in the fourth quarter of an April 19 game at  
New Jersey. Jones missed the next three games. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones played 41 minutes and scored 21 points Wednesday in  
Charlotte's season finale at Boston. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones came to Charlotte from the Los Angeles Lakers in a trade  
that also included center Elden Campbell in exchange for Glen Rice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
