<HEADLINE> Mail Carriers To Begin Food Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Mail carriers across the country will conduct  
their annual Stamp Out Hunger campaign Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Carriers in some 10,000 communities will collect nonperishable  
food donations as they deliver mail along their normal routes, the 
National Association of Letter Carriers said. 
</P>
<P>
	People who want to make donations can leave cans or boxes of  
food near their mailbox before the carrier arrives. These will be 
taken to local post offices and then delivered to local food banks, 
pantries or shelters. 
