<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cox Radio Buying Athens Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Cox Radio, Inc. has signed an agreement with  
Clarke Broadcasting Corporation to acquire WNGC-FM in Athens for 
$78 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The purchase includes a federal permit to relocate and construct  
a new tower. Cox hopes to complete the purchase by the end of 1999. 
</P>
<P>
	``The tower move enables this frequency to continue to serve  
Athens but also additional communities in central and eastern 
Georgia,'' Cox President and Chief Executive Officer Robert F. Neil 
said in a statement Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Cox is the fifth largest radio company in the United States  
based on revenue, with 58 stations in 12 markets. 


</P>
</TEXT>
