<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-06 07:55:00 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Churchill To Buy Hollywood Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Churchill Downs announced an agreement  
today to purchase Hollywood Park race track for $140 million, 
giving the Louisville track a foothold on both coasts while 
broadening its simulcast operations. 
</P>
<P>
	The purchase of the southern California track follows Churchill  
Downs' purchase of Calder Racecourse in Miami for $86 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Hollywood Park officials said the deal would generate money for  
its expanding gaming interest. 
</P>
<P>
	Under the deal, Churchill Downs will acquire 237 of Hollywood  
Park's 378 acres, which includes the Inglewood, Calif., track, 
other real estate around the track and a casino. Hollywood Park 
will lease the casino, a California card club, from Churchill Downs 
for $3 million per year. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal is subject to approval by the California Horse Racing  
Board, and is expected to close in the third quarter of this year. 
</P>
<P>
	Hollywood Park officials said some money from the sale will be  
used to develop its hotel and riverboat casino in Indiana, 
scheduled to open next year upstream from Louisville. Hollywood 
Park also will seek to develop the remaining 141 acres it will own 
at near the track, or field offers from potential buyers. 
</P>
<P>
	``This transaction is a major step toward the attainment of our  
corporate objective of focusing on the growth of our gaming 
businesses,'' said R.D. Hubbard, Hollywood Park's chief executive 
officer. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal with Churchill Downs also will ensure continued live  
racing at Hollywood Park, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Churchill Downs has racing and simulcast wagering operations at  
Ellis Park in Henderson, Hoosier Park in Anderson, Ind., as well as 
a minority interest in Kentucky Downs in Franklin. It also holds 
interests in various other racing services companies. Churchill 
Downs, home of the Kentucky Derby, is the company's flagship 
operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
