<HEADLINE> Facts on the Plains Tornadoes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEATHS: At least 41 in Oklahoma, five in Kansas from Monday's  
storms; one in Texas on Tuesday; four in Tennessee on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	INJURIES: 748 in Oklahoma, nearly 150 in Kansas, more than 12 in  
Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	PROPERTY DAMAGE: Nearly 3,000 homes and 47 businesses destroyed  
in Oklahoma; 1,500 buildings destroyed in Kansas. Two dozen homes 
and a church damaged or destroyed in Arkansas; about seven blocks 
of DeKalb, Texas, demolished and 150 homes damaged. 
</P>
