	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Pinch-runner Kevin Stocker scored  
the go-ahead run on an eighth-inning wild pitch by Jose Santiago 
and Fred McGriff homered again as the Tampa Bay Devil Rays beat the 
Kansas City Royals 5-4 this afternoon. McGriff hit a blast to 
center field in the second inning for his 10th homer and fifth in 
the past five games. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by JEROME MINERVA  
