<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 40 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened lower. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is down 40 points in today's early going. Losers 
on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 4-3 lead over gainers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is down three points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is down three points. 
</P>
<P>
	Interest rate worries are reappearing on Wall Street.  
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the Treasury's benchmark bond has risen above five  
and three-quarter percent, a level not seen in some time. 
</P>
<P>
	The bond market's bearish sentiment comes with Alan Greenspan  
speaking to a banking conference this morning in Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
	And tomorrow, the government releases its April unemployment  
report, considered the key economic statistic of the month. 
</P>
<P>
	European stock market averages, which had been higher, are now  
edging lower. 
</P>
