<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Minister Lifts Suspension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) -- Hungary's sports and youth minister  
Thursday lifted the suspension of Hungarian Soccer Federation 
president Attila Kovacs. 
</P>
<P>
	The action, which will be effective Monday, ended more than  
three months of wrangling between the ministry and FIFA, the 
international soccer federation. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am withdrawing my suspension of the federation's  
president,'' Tamas Deutsch told TV3, citing pressure from FIFA. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel one must bow before such overwhelming power,'' Deutsch  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Later in the day he met with Kovacs and made the announcement  
official. 
</P>
<P>
	When Deutsch suspended Kovacs, he said it was because of  
questions concerning the federation's finances. 
</P>
<P>
	Kovacs said Thursday that an audit will be done and should be  
completed next month. 
</P>
<P>
	FIFA general secretary Michel Zen-Ruffinen had told Deutsch to  
restore Kovacs immediately or face a suspension of the entire 
Hungarian soccer federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
